ivery: How Can We Connect the Dots’?, she explained that the Internet offers rich resources for authentic inquiry and librarians must learn to orchestrate sophisticated strategies to become literate in the complex environment. The don said that re-skilling and re-tooling of academic libraries in line with global best standards must not be overlooked if the country wants to turnout quality research outputs that would proffer solutions to the myriad of problems staring the nation in the face. Falana absent as FG arraigns Sowore(Opens in a new browser tab) She bemoaned what she called “severe national library budget cuts,” which according to her, has made it impossible for academic libraries in Nigeria to thrive in the face of new innovations creeping into the profession. In his remarks, the Vice Chancellor of the institution, Prof. Charles Igwe, described the lecturer as a sound administrator whose contributions in efficient management of the library has earned the university the top spot in Nigeria as the university with highest scholarly citations according to Google Webometric ranking. The Vice Chancellor who was represented by his deputy in  , Prof. Patrick Okpoko, also revealed that plans are on to make the university administration paperless by investing in ICTs and improving the competency of both staff and students. Vanguard FORMER Minister of Defense, Dr Olu Agunloye has advocated for the introduction of Information Communication Technology (ICT) into the library system in the nation education sector. November 9, 2010 In "Technology" The 10th Nigeria International Book Fair(NIBF), which officially opened with book exhibition at the Multi-purpose Halls of the University of Lagos, Akoka, Lagos, on Monday, 9th May, 2011 came to its high point on Tuesday, 10th with a critical appraisal of the impact of new technologies on the African Book… May 19, 2011 In "The Arts" Vice President, Arc. Namadi Sambo, was in Nsukka last week to put a seal of authority to plans by 